/// # Verum Runtime Module (core/runtime)
///
/// Unified runtime infrastructure implementing the Modular Runtime Architecture.
/// Provides configurable runtime support for diverse target platforms:
///
/// - `@cfg(runtime = "full")`: Full async with work-stealing, heap, threads
/// - `@cfg(runtime = "single_thread")`: Single-threaded async (WASM, embedded)
/// - `@cfg(runtime = "no_async")`: Synchronous mode with blocking I/O
/// - `@cfg(runtime = "no_heap")`: Stack-only allocation (real-time, safety-critical)
/// - `@cfg(runtime = "embedded")`: Minimal core intrinsics only (microcontrollers)
///
/// ## Architecture
///
/// ```
/// ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
/// │                       MODULAR RUNTIME ARCHITECTURE                         │
/// ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
/// │                                                                            │
/// │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐     │
/// │  │   ASYNC     │   │    HEAP     │   │  THREADING  │   │     IO      │     │
/// │  │  EXECUTOR   │   │  ALLOCATOR  │   │    POOL     │   │   DRIVER    │     │
/// │  └──────┬──────┘   └──────┬──────┘   └──────┬──────┘   └──────┬──────┘     │
/// │         │                 │                 │                 │            │
/// │         ▼                 ▼                 ▼                 ▼            │
/// │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
/// │  │                      RUNTIME FACADE                                 │   │
/// │  │  RuntimeConfig protocol + ExecutionEnv (θ+)                         │   │
/// │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
/// │                                    │                                       │
/// │                                    ▼                                       │
/// │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
/// │  │                      V-LLSI KERNEL (always)                         │   │
/// │  │  • sys.syscall intrinsics  • Atomic operations  • TLS bootstrap     │   │
/// │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
/// │                                                                            │
/// └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
/// ```
///
/// ## ExecutionEnv (θ+) - Four Pillars
///
/// Every task executes within an ExecutionEnv providing:
/// 1. **Memory**: CBGR tier, allocator, shared registry
/// 2. **Capabilities**: Static dependencies + dynamic contexts
/// 3. **Error Recovery**: Supervision, circuit breakers, retry policies
/// 4. **Concurrency**: Executor handle, isolation model, parallelism config
///
/// ## Zero FFI Architecture
///
/// All operations use sys-subsystem calls via VBC intrinsics:
/// - Memory: `sys.mmap`, `sys.munmap` → VBC opcode 0xF1
/// - I/O: `sys.io_uring_enter`, `sys.kqueue` → VBC opcode 0xF4
/// - Sync: `sys.futex`, `sys.atomic_*` → VBC opcode 0xF2
/// - Time: `sys.clock_gettime` → VBC opcode 0xF5
///
/// ## Performance Targets
///
/// | Metric                | Target     | V-LLSI    |
/// |-----------------------|------------|-----------|
/// | Context lookup        | < 10ns     | ~2ns      |
/// | Task spawn overhead   | < 200ns    | ~150ns    |
/// | Memory per task       | < 4KB      | ~2.5KB    |
/// | Allocations per spawn | 0          | 0 (stack) |

module runtime;

